{
  "texts": [
    "[20] conducted experiments on two tasks involving medical images: classifying skin conditions based on images from the digital camera and labelling chest radiographs with multiple labels.",
    "They found that using self-supervised learning on ImageNet, followed by additional self-supervised learning using specific unlabelled medical images, significantly improved the accuracy of medical image classification compared to using only TL from IamgeNet labelled images.",
    "Raghu, Maithra et al.",
    "[19] have shown that using a different domain as a source of TL does not significantly impact the performance of medical imaging tasks.",
    "Lightweight models trained from scratch can carry out almost as well as models transferred from ImageNet."
  ]
}